quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,53,"Say: ‘You that serve Me, who have sinned against your souls, do not despair of God‘s mercy, assuredly God forgives all sins. He it is who is the Forgiving One, the Compassionate"
  39,54,"Turn in penitence to your Lord, and submit to Him before the scourge overtakes you; for then there will be none to help you"
  39,55,"Follow the best of what is revealed to you by your Lord before the scourge suddenly smites you, when you are unaware"
  39,56,"lest any soul should say: \"Alas! I neglected my duty to God and scoffed with the scoffers"
  39,57,"Or should say: \"If God had guided me I would have feared Him"
  39,58,"Or, should say, when it sees the scourge: \"Could I but live again, I would lead a righteous life"
  39,59,"Yes, indeed. My revelations did come to you; but you denied them. You were arrogant and a blasphemer.\"‘"
  39,60,"And on the Day of Resurrection you shall see their faces blackened, those who uttered falsehoods about God. Is there not in Hell a resting-place for the arrogant"
  39,61,"But God will deliver those who fear Him, for they have earned salvation. Evil shall not strike them, nor shall they ever grieve"
  39,62,"God is the Creator of all things, and of all things He is the Guardian"
  39,63,His are the keys of the heavens and the earth. And those that deny God‘s revelations will surely be lost